== Potatoes ==

Fill and boil your kettle. When boiling, pour the water into a #sauce pan{} with
@salt{0.5%tsp} and pop on to boil.

Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!).

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through,
~{15-20%minutes}.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced).

Trim the @green beans{80}(trimmed).

Trim the @spring onion{1}(trimmed then sliced thinly).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30}.

== Smokey Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium high heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the @British chicken thighs{4} and sliced onion, fry
until the chicken is browned on each side and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}.
Turn every 2-3 mins.

After ~{8%minutes}, add the @chicken stock powder{1}, @BBQ sauce{32} and @water{75}.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened
and the chicken is cooked through, another ~{6-7%minutes}.

> Add a splash more water if dry. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer
> pink in the middle.

== Garlicky Green Beans ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small frying pan on a medium high heat. When hot add
the green beans and a splash of water and cover with a #lid{}.

Cook covered for ~{3-4%minutes}, remove the lid add the garlic and cook for a
further ~{1%minute}.

Remove from the heat, and set aside. Cover with the lid to keep warm.

== Cheesy Mash ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan off the
heat.

Add the cheddar cheese and spring onion, a @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{splas} and
mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Cover with a lid to keep warm.

Once the chicken is cooked, taste the sauce and season with salt and pepper if
needed.

== To Serve ==

Share the mash between your plates.

Pop the smoky chicken and onion alongside.

Share the green beans between your plates.

Enjoy!